defaultPoor health is a well established consequence of 
defaulthomelessness
default;
default this can include 
defaultchronic conditions as well as anxiety, stress, self-harm, other mental health problems and infectious diseases. A significant minority of homeless people are dependent on drugs or alcohol often alongside mental health problems and other m
defaultultiple needs
default. 
default&#xa0;
default4.3
default              
defaultAn increase in h
defaultealth problems 
defaultis
default not confined to those sleeping rough. People living in temporary accommodation, with friends or in hostels have little stability, often have to share kitchens and bathrooms and have little privacy or security
default. They may also experience problems relating t
defaulto damp or overcrowded conditions. Research also shows that homeless families in rural areas may spend longer in temporary accommodation than those in urban areas
default and that
default health problems arising from such circumstances include an increased risk of dermato
defaultlogical problems, musculoskeletal problems, poor obstetric outcomes and a range of mental health problems.  
default&#xa0;
default4.4
default              
defaultThe effect on children in homeless families living in temporary accommodation can be serious
default. There are many detrimental effects on the physi
defaultcal and emotional development of children living in unsettled or overcrowded accommodation with little room to play or do homework. Studies have shown children in these circumstances 
defaultare more likely to experience
default behavioural disturbance, have higher levels of illness and infection, have poor sleep patterns and are more prone to accidental injury
default.
default&#xa0;
default4.5
default              
defaultIt can be more difficult for homeless people to sustain continuity of care, to meet appointments made a long time 
defaultin advance, or to participate in health 
defaultimprovement and health promotion activities, such as healthy eating and physical activity
default. 
